<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF2014E63A5F16F92CB88E4" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF2014E63A5F16F92CB88E4" blockId="16.[151,760,367,966]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E63A5F16F92698AA4" bold="true" box="[151,280,367,390]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Comments.</emphasis>
The correct generic assignment of this species remains unclear. 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E6266F18F928F8A84" author="JACOBY M." box="[340,510,399,422]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="377 - 501" part="36" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." title="Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1896" yearSuffix="a">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
described it from two specimens (according to a note mentioned in the same paper in the description of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E6281F1CF91B38AC4" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[435,706,463,486]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E6281F1CF91B38AC4" box="[435,706,463,486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Platyxantha submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and classified it in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E6219F1EF92DA8924" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1864" box="[299,427,495,518]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E6219F1EF92DA8924" box="[299,427,495,518]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Platyxantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E6194F1EF93908904" author="WILCOX J. A." editor="WILCOX J. A." firstAuthor="WILCOX" journalOrPublisher="Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." title="Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3)." year="1973">WILCOX (1973)</bibRefCitation>
. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E6266F20F92A38904" author="REID C. A. M." box="[340,466,527,550]" firstAuthor="REID" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Entomology" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 9" part="38" refId="ref33192" refString="REID C. A. M. 1999: Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Australian Journal of Entomology 38: 1 - 9." title="Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae)" type="journal article" year="1999">REID (1999)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E61B3F20F91898904" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[641,760,527,550]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E61B3F20F91898904" box="[641,760,527,550]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any comments. I examined both 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E6104F22F91E08964" box="[566,657,559,582]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">syntypes</typeStatus>
(females) deposited in the BMNH and MSNG. The BMNH 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E6197F24F91898944" box="[677,760,591,614]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">syntype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFF2014E63ADF26F938C89A4" box="[159,253,623,646]" captionStart="Figs 94–104" captionStartId="20.[151,187,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,190,1594]" captionTargetId="figure-13@20.[151,1437,190,1595]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 94–104. Habitus of Taumacera. 94– T.variceps (Laboissière, 1933) (male); 95 – T.viridis (Hope, 1831) (male, syntype); 96 – T.coxalis (Jacoby, 1899) (female, syntype); 97 – T. jacobyi Weise, 1922 (male, syntype of Dorydea costatipennis Jacoby, 1896); 98 – T. javanensis Jacoby, 1895 (male, syntype); 99 – T. kinabaluensis (Mohamedsaid, 1995) (male); 100 – T. monstrosa (Jacoby, 1899) (male); 101 – T. multicostata (Jacoby, 1896) (female, syntype); 102 – T. submetallica (Jacoby, 1896) (female, syntype); 103 – T. sumatrana (Jacoby, 1899) (male); 104 – T. variabilis (Jacoby, 1891) (male, syntype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505540/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
) was studied in detail. It has closed posterior margins of the procoxal cavity and the metatibia without a spine. However, the legs are in bad condition and I cannot exclude that the spines were broken. The correct generic placement can be resolved only when a male specimen is discovered. Moreover, it cannot be excluded that 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E61F8F30F92F68864" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicostata">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E61F8F30F92F68864" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Platyxantha multicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E62F1F32F911C8864" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[451,621,815,838]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E62F1F32F911C8864" box="[451,621,815,838]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to a single species as they were collected in the same locality (Si-Rambé) and differ only in body length and paler colouration of the elytral disc in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E62F6F38F91138884" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[452,610,911,934]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E62F6F38F91138884" box="[452,610,911,934]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as mentioned already by 
